<section class="instructions">
  <h1>See it live!</h1>
  <p>We just created a new app! Let's see it live.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      Move into your new application folder
    </li>
    <pre><code>$ cd ~/Desktop/sample_app</code></pre>
    <li>
      We're going to start a little server so we can see the application in a browser
    </li>
    <pre><code>$ rails server</code></pre>
    <p>This command should show you:</p>
    <pre><code>=> Booting WEBrick
=> Rails 4.0.0 application starting in development on http://0.0.0.0:3000
=> Run `rails server -h` for more startup options
=> Ctrl-C to shutdown server
[2013-08-01 16:37:03] INFO  WEBrick 1.3.1
[2013-08-01 16:37:03] INFO  ruby 2.0.0 (2013-05-14) [x86_64-darwin12.4.0]
[2013-08-01 16:37:03] INFO  WEBrick::HTTPServer#start: pid=12109 port=3000</code></pre>
    <p>Note that you'll no longer be able to type anything in this window. You can close the server by hitting <strong>Control + C</strong></p>
    <li>Open up your browser and visit <%= link_to "http://localhost:3000", "http://localhost:3000", target: "_blank" %></li>
    <li>You should see your new web app!</li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section class="prompt">
  <%= link_to "Yay! What's next?", next_wizard_path, class: "option" %>
</section>
